name: Selmer Paris 52AXOS Alto Saxophone
description: Professional Selmer Alto Sax. Perfect condition and barely used. No mouthpiece or reeds included. Does come with a nice neckstrap.

name: PRS SE Custom Electric Guitar
description: This baby's been on tour around the world so it's a little worn but plays beautifully. Has a warm tone and great character. Very Versatile

name: Native Instruments KOMPLETE KONTROL S88 Keyboard
description: Lightly used, my son gave up trying to be a music producer so I'm basically giving this thing away. Damn kid gives up on everything smh.

name: Didgeridoo
description: Don't know the brand but it plays fine. Not real eucalyptus, I think it's made out of PVC pipe. Anyway, it's a good deal.

name: C.G. Conn 6D Artist Intermediate Double French Horn
description: Good French Horn for any band student. My husband dropped it a few times so it has some dings and dents. One of the valves is a little sticky too. Otherwise it's good to go.

name: Crestwood Acoustic Guitar
description: Super cheap off-brand guitar I found in my basement. Got some water damage, honestly it's a pretty messed up guitar but might make some kid's day.

name: Scherl & Roth SR55E4H 4/4 Size Galliard Student Cello
description: My daughter took very good care of this Cello. Comes with a bow and case. Perfect for starter students.

name: Yamaha Stage Custom Birch Shell Pack Drum Set
description: Could not take how loud my wife is when she plays these things. Switched her to an electric set and am selling this off. Great condidtion, had seen many bar venues in the 90's so may smell a little smokey.

name: Yamaha YCL-622 II Professional Bb Bass Clarinet
description: SERIOUS BUYERS ONLY. This Bass Clarinet has been in many concert halls. Played mostly with the Detroit Symphony Orchestra. Perfect condition.

name: Ableton Push 2
description: Good condition. Does not come with Ableton Live Software, or any cables so you'll have to order those seperatly
